N.B. CMP, CPX, and CPY all set flags according to:

    A, X, or Y < Memory  --->  N=1, Z=0, C=0
    A, X, or Y = Memory  --->  N=0, Z=1, C=1
    A, X, or Y > Memory  --->  N=0, Z=0, C=1

